Job Description:Duties
Curators in Content Development take a key role in developing and delivering major projects related to exhibitions, collections, 
research, products and other programs. They also represent the Museum in internal and external forums and help develop the 
institutions curatorial practice. They are responsible for:
	Developing and researching the National Historical Collection and contributing to the development of collections policy and 
systems;
	Leading research and development of content for permanent galleries, temporary and travelling exhibitions, public programs, 
publications, and other products;
	Developing work plans and managing budgets for teams on specific projects;
	Liaising with colleagues in business units across the Museum in delivering the key outputs listed above;
	Consulting with stakeholders and representing the Museum in external and internal forums and discussions as required;
	Servicing content needs of other business units throughout the Museum as required.

